==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Auric
<hw>Au"ric</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>aurum</ets>
gold.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to gold.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, or derived from,
gold; -- said of those compounds of gold in which this element has its
higher valence; <as>as, <ex>auric</ex> oxide; <ex>auric</ex>
chloride.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Aurichalceous</ent>⟦br⟧
